cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on adversarial attacks in the context of image classification, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of Wasserstein distance as a threat model also suggests that it may be relevant to researchers in optimization (cs.NE), as well as those studying security and privacy (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
